Let's get into scripture

We're continuing our slow walk through sermon on the mount, according to the gospel of Matthew

Sermon on the mount was Jesus' longest continual teaching and is perhaps the most famous sermon ever given

It spans chapter 5-7 in the gospel of Matthew. Last week we finished Matthew chapter 5 and we're now starting chapter 6

Todsy we're covering verses 1-15 where Jesus talks about giving to the needy and also teaches us a very clear model and template for prayer with the Lords prayer

In fellowship II in April, we covered prayer as a core Christian behaviour and I used covered 6 verses 5-15 to unpack the prayer template that Jesus gave us

Today we're going to revisit that template and talk about it again

While prayer will mean different things to different people and we will all pray in our own way, Jesus delivers a very clear instruction here in Sermon on the mount about how to pray

Let's read the word


--> Matthew chapter 6 verses 1-4

So far in sermon on the mount, Jesus has emphasized that righteousness includes a persons heart (their thoughts and attitudes) just as much as their outward behaviours

Our inner disposition is more important than our outward disposition

Jesus is emphasizing that what matters to him most is our heart more than our deeds

He's telling us to beware of trying to appear righteous to others. If others see our good deeds, we've received our rewards and will get no bonus points from the father 

We shouldn't yell from the rooftops or brag to others when we give to the needy. We shouldnt sound a trumpet

The point of giving is to glorify God the father, not to glorify us as the givers

If we seek praise and recognition for our giving, we are not doing it from our heart but to receive a reward. If we receive that reward from others, we get no reward from The Father

God will notice and reward those who give in humility and sincerity. He won't notice those who give boastfully and out of desire to receive recognition for their giving


Giving: money, attention, love. Money is a representation of our time but the most scarce and precious thing we can give is our time and attention to those who need it

Opening the door for someone is a form of giving

Letting someone in while driving is a form of giving

Offering money to those who need it is a form of giving




God rewards righteous behaviours done from the heart to glorify his goodness. He doesn't reward behaviiours done to gain the praise and admiration of others even if they seem righteous on the surface 

Those who give to receive praise will receive temporary recognition which is meaningless. Thats their reward

Those who give to glorify God will receive eternal favour and recognition from the father. A much better reward in my opinion

Don't let worldly praise motivation our actions

Doing the right thing for the wrong reason is not righteous, it's egotism

Give to help others, not for praise or recognition from others 

Phillip Anthony Mitchell said it perfectly: Don't give to be seen, Just be seen being generous

Our motives tell us a out our heart. Its not about our behaviours, its about our motives. God cares about our motives which are a deeper layer than just the behaviours we do


Now lets move on to verses 5-15 which is arguably the most important teaching on prayer written anywhere in scripture

--> Matthew chapter 6 verses 5-15

Do not be like the hippocrites

The hippocrites pray to be seen praying by others

If someone is praying to be seen by others, they will not be seen by good

Their praise from others for praying is their reward

Jesus says and WHEN you pray. Not IF you pray. Jesus is assuming that his followers will be praying

Mandatory behaviour

When assumes that one must have a prayer life. Jesus expects us to have a lifestyle that includes prayer. He wants to be hearing your voice regularly

Being prayerless we become distant from God

Prayer is communication to God. Lack of communication to God is a vulnerability to communication by the devil

We're either voluntarily speaking with God or we will be involuntarily spoken to and influenced by the devil

Prayer is protection

Don't be unprotected and vulnerable

Be locked into the shield of Gods protection which is present through prayer 

Sounds like the same lesson we just covered. Don't give to be seen giving, just be seen giving

Don't pray to be seen praying. In fact, when you pray, do it in secret. Speak to our heavenly father in secret and he will reward you












